				<div class="box">
			<h3>Editorial comment</h3>
			<p>The contrasting trends in banana exports to the EU in 2010 for the traditional Windward Island exporters, whose production was devastated by cyclones, and for the non-traditional and re-emergent ACP banana exporters such as the Dominican Republic, Ghana and Suriname are indicative of the longer-term trend under way, as highlighted in the European Parliament research report. In 2010, these three ACP exporters were well placed to capitalise on the higher prices arising from lower production in Ecuador and Colombia, whose exports to the EU fell by 6% and 3% compared to 2009.</p><p>These trends reinforce the European Parliament research report’s findings that banana accompanying measures assistance should be focused on traditional Caribbean banana exporters. One important potential area of support for such assistance could be the development of local and regional demand-and-supply capacities for banana and banana products.</p>
		</div>
		
